Creates or updates a lemma as part of your proof. Lemmas are keyed by name,
so you can make multiple lemmas as needed. The name of the lemma in the provided
code must match the provided `name` field. The lemma must be a complete
Lean `theorem` statement and proof. It will be inserted directly above the theorem in the source file.
Use this whenever you need additional components/sub-theorems to complete the proof.
You can only update lemmas you created; attempting to overwrite a pre-existing lemma
will fail. The provided code will completely overwrite any existing code for that lemma.
Any use of `sorry` will be rejected. Provide an empty `code` string to delete a lemma you created,
which you should do whenever you find a lemma was unnecessary to complete the proof.